Description: Body sherd of black-figured pottery cup or phiale; interior glazed with decoration in added white and incision: torso and arm of a figure reclining (? or falling back?) to left (incision including two lines across waist and over left arm below elbow; perhaps pale orange lines for cross straps on chest); exterior: large, loose, palmette, with thin, wavy petals (one red); to its left uncertain remains, perhaps the lowered arm of a figure with the back of the neck; red remains on arm, possible white on neck.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B102.36)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.244)
